        "title": "fix(ui): scroll to cron run history",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Mark the existing Run history card as the scroll target on the cron page.\n- After clicking a job's History button, keep loading that job's runs and scroll the Run history card into view.\n- Add a focused cron view test for the visible-feedback behavior.\n\nCloses #59902\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run ui/src/ui/views/cron.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: On `/cron`, clicking a job's History button gives visible feedback by scrolling the existing Run history card into view after loading that job's runs.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on this PR branch (`codex/cron-history-scroll-59902-20260618`) with repository dependencies available, rendering the changed cron view through the repository UI test harness.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run ui/src/ui/views/cron.test.ts --reporter=verbose\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: Terminal capture from the local OpenClaw cron UI render run showed the changed behavior:\n\n```text\n✓ |ui| ui/src/ui/views/cron.test.ts > cron view > scrolls the run history card into view when History is clicked\n\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  15 passed (15)\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 1.09s\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The rendered cron view test verifies clicking History calls `onLoadRuns(\"job-1\")` and scrolls the Run history target with `{ behavior: \"smooth\", block: \"start\" }`; `git diff --check` produced no output.\n\nWhat was not tested: Browser screenshot proof was not captured in this environment; the focused UI rendering path above verifies the changed DOM behavior for the affected cron view.\n",
